The paper discusses the use of multi-agent systems and market-oriented programming in climate control, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the advantages and weaknesses of these systems, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control engineering (cs.SY). The comparison between decentralized markets and central control involves optimization and decision-making, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
